Package: depgraph
Title: Dataset Dependency Graphs for Leakage-Aware Machine Learning
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person(
      given = "bioLeak",
      family = "Developers",
      email = "maintainer@example.org",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Build typed dependency graphs for biomedical datasets so that
    sample structure, provenance, and leakage-relevant relationships can be
    represented explicitly, validated, queried, and converted into
    machine-learning split constraints. The package supports dependency-aware
    graph construction, structural and leakage-relevant validation,
    sample-level dependency queries, graph-derived split-constraint
    generation, and translation of those constraints into 'bioLeak'-ready
    split specifications for trustworthy model evaluation workflows.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    graphics,
    igraph
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
NeedsCompilation: no
